<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-27T19:02:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-27T19:02:00-05:00" n="930" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.48/8</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Thurston</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-27T18:00:00-06:02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 27, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Shocks continue. Water situation becoming serious, sanitary conditions
                            correspondingly affected. Mr. Clark, President local chapter American
                            Red Cross offers funds collected to date for relief work. Amount five
                            hundred dollars. Shall I accept and place disposition Government?
                            Destruction continues and thousands now shelterless. Weather mild,
                            foreign colonies safe. Request acknowledgment every message.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>